WorkItem.Description:
Intellisense for 'this' is incorrect inside object literal.

__Example__

```
interface ISample {
    prop: number;
}

class Test {

    public anotherProp: number;

    public foo(): ISample {
        return { prop: this.anotherProp };
    }

}
```

In the above the suggestion for the 'this.' typed while trying to assign the 'prop' (from the foo) is not correct. The suggestion given is 'this.prop' however what we want and compiles is 'this.anotherProp'

This can be related to the issue with the following id: 767.
